   415вҶ’## API Reference вҖҰ
   417вҶ’### `match`
   419вҶ’```ts
   420вҶ’match(value);
   421вҶ’```
   422вҶ’
   423вҶ’Create a `Match` object on which you can later call `.with`, `.when`, `.otherwise` and `.run`.
   424вҶ’
   742вҶ’## Patterns вҖҰ
   857вҶ’#### `P._` wildcard
   859вҶ’The `P._` pattern will match any value. You can also use `P.any`, which is an alias to `P._`.
   860вҶ’
   861вҶ’```ts
   862вҶ’import { match, P } from 'ts-pattern';
   863вҶ’
   864вҶ’const input = 'hello';
   865вҶ’
   866вҶ’const output = match(input)
   867вҶ’  .with(P._, () => 'It will always match')
   868вҶ’  // OR
   869вҶ’  .with(P.any, () => 'It will always match')
   870вҶ’  .otherwise(() => 'This string will never be used');
   871вҶ’
   872вҶ’console.log(output);
   873вҶ’// => 'It will always match'
   874вҶ’```
   875вҶ’
  1405вҶ’## `P.string` predicates вҖҰ
  1500вҶ’## `P.number` and `P.bigint` predicates вҖҰ
  1621вҶ’## Types вҖҰ
  1623вҶ’### `P.infer`
  1625вҶ’`P.infer<typeof somePattern>` lets you infer a type of value from a type of pattern.
  1626вҶ’
  1627вҶ’It's particularly useful when validating an API response.
  1628вҶ’
  1629вҶ’```ts
  1630вҶ’const postPattern = {
  1631вҶ’  title: P.string,
  1632вҶ’  content: P.string,
  1633вҶ’  stars: P.number.between(1, 5).optional(),
  1634вҶ’  author: {
  1635вҶ’    firstName: P.string,
  1636вҶ’    lastName: P.string.optional(),
  1637вҶ’    followerCount: P.number,
  1638вҶ’  },
  1639вҶ’} as const;
  1640вҶ’
  1641вҶ’type Post = P.infer<typeof postPattern>;
  1642вҶ’
  1643вҶ’// posts: Post[]
  1644вҶ’const posts = await fetch(someUrl)
  1645вҶ’  .then((res) => res.json())
  1646вҶ’  .then((res: unknown): Post[] =>
  1647вҶ’    isMatching({ data: P.array(postPattern) }, res) ? res.data : []
  1648вҶ’  );
  1649вҶ’```
  1650вҶ’
